                      "type": "Words",
                      "data": {
                        "value": ". If the Jacobian has only few non-zero elements in *each* row, providing the sparsity structure will greatly speed up the computations [4]_. A zero entry means that a corresponding element in the Jacobian is always zero. If None (default), the Jacobian is assumed to be dense."
